<br>
Bid 0. If the opponent let you go first, that is fine. You hope you have enough stealths to make it through to Ford of Bruinen. You don&#39;t mind going second to allow Hollin to be played. <br>
<br>
The fellowship side should be easy to play. Just try to stay alive, and hope that your shadow side catches your opponent unaware, especially if he&#39;s unprepared for the Balrog-snowbomb. The shadow side is some sort of an Uruk swarm with power-ups to damage the opponent&#39;s fellowship.<br>
<br>
Good luck, and enjoy. If you lose, don&#39;t worry. If you win, GLOAT AS MUCH AS YOU CAN!!! :)  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
